This paper deals with the formal specification and verification of distributed systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of automata to characterise and synthesise global session types, which is related to the sub-category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of distributed communication, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of labelled transition systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of compatibility between multiple parties, which is related to the sub-category of Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL).
